properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 10 at 3:44PM CST until January 12 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Chicago IL
properties.description:
...Periods of Wintry Precipitation, Possibly Significant, Tonight
Through Saturday Night...

* WHAT...Rain is likely to change over to a period of light
freezing rain and sleet late tonight into Saturday morning.
Total ice accumulations of up to one tenth of an inch is
possible, with some light sleet accumulation also possible.
While precipitation may lighten in intensity Saturday late
morning through mid afternoon, a period of snow is likely
Saturday evening. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches are
possible. Northeast winds will gust as high as 45 mph overnight
into Saturday and combined with ice and snow may cause further
impacts.

* WHERE...Lake IL and Kane Counties.

* WHEN...From 3 AM Saturday to 3 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could become impacted at times very late
tonight into Saturday, and then again later Saturday afternoon
into Saturday night. Patchy blowing snow could significantly
reduce visibility later Saturday afternoon and night.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for Illinois can be obtained on the
internet at www.gettingaroundillinois.com. The latest road
conditions for Indiana are available by calling 18002617623.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM SATURDAY TO 3 AM CST SUNDAY
